    {
      "id": "zYpCsK3PJJX4eU0eaF6Hn",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 263.2615699866577,
      "y": -8969.99499047346,
      "width": 1161.4393310546875,
      "height": 525,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#343a40",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 90,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bI4",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 338044088,
      "version": 1138,
      "versionNonce": 371336136,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1772711869684,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "1. Service networking\n\n   1. service talks via TCP/UDP. TCP ensures ordered delivery, UDP used in video system. \n   2. Multiple layers of networking in OSI model.\n We work on application layer(7th): main protocol is HTTP\nThen presentation layer(6th): it has ssl and tls\nimportant ones are transport(4th) and networking(3rd) layer. The main protocols are IP , TCP and UDP. \n\nhttp client -> server\n  short lived connection\n\ngRPC: remote procedural call. based on proto or binary serialization not human friendly.\nIt is fast. \nIt is said that the connection is long live and always runs on HTTP 2. A single connection can have multiple requests. \n\nLoad balancer levels: L4/L7 (used in apps for http)\n   L4 is used for websocket ones. \n\nLong polling: the http is short lived, so some custom code will lie on server side, \n\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1. Service networking\n\n   1. service talks via TCP/UDP. TCP ensures ordered delivery, UDP used in video system. \n   2. Multiple layers of networking in OSI model.\n We work on application layer(7th): main protocol is HTTP\nThen presentation layer(6th): it has ssl and tls\nimportant ones are transport(4th) and networking(3rd) layer. The main protocols are IP , TCP and UDP. \n\nhttp client -> server\n  short lived connection\n\ngRPC: remote procedural call. based on proto or binary serialization not human friendly.\nIt is fast. \nIt is said that the connection is long live and always runs on HTTP 2. A single connection can have multiple requests. \n\nLoad balancer levels: L4/L7 (used in apps for http)\n   L4 is used for websocket ones. \n\nLong polling: the http is short lived, so some custom code will lie on server side, \n\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "1xJRTCw7umU6kUDoNN-px",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 234.38926663202938,
      "y": -8419.334751688408,
      "width": 329.499755859375,
      "height": 175,
      "angle": 0,
