      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1772711921923,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "2. api design:\n  based on resources.\n\nget, put, post, patch, delete. \n  creation of resource in post\n  put is idempotent, is full update\n  patch is partial update ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "2. api design:\n  based on resources.\n\nget, put, post, patch, delete. \n  creation of resource in post\n  put is idempotent, is full update\n  patch is partial update ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "WBzoTep8QcgBDJceFGSpE",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 760.4358205974667,
      "y": -8400.552445106918,
      "width": 682.4195556640625,
      "height": 325,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#343a40",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 90,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bI6",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1991009208,
      "version": 551,
      "versionNonce": 740404168,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1772712427617,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Get API paging:\n\n1. offset kind:\napi/users?limit=10&offset=10\nmeans data after first 10 will be returned and 10 values will be given. \nIt does not handle when new data is being added.\n\n\n2. cursor kind:\napi/users?limit=10&cursor=abc\nhere in DB proper check is done if cursor value is larger than abc,\nthen 10 values are returned. \nLittle tough to implement but better.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Get API paging:\n\n1. offset kind:\napi/users?limit=10&offset=10\nmeans data after first 10 will be returned and 10 values will be given. \nIt does not handle when new data is being added.\n\n\n2. cursor kind:\napi/users?limit=10&cursor=abc\nhere in DB proper check is done if cursor value is larger than abc,\nthen 10 values are returned. \nLittle tough to implement but better.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "_kahOYQ2D8CTmJGicQ4Lh",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 194.41223121792865,
      "y": -7958.353899855512,
      "width": 878.79931640625,
      "height": 275,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#343a40",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
