      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1772712174046,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "3. Data modelling:\n\npostgres: constraints on columns.\n | single node.\n - start with normalization and if needed then only change.\n - sharding can be done from user side, there is no constraint. Sharding main issue is that\ncross shard complex queries.\n\nmongo DB, dynamo: schemaless and good on writes.\ndynamo DB: partition key and sorting key.\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "3. Data modelling:\n\npostgres: constraints on columns.\n | single node.\n - start with normalization and if needed then only change.\n - sharding can be done from user side, there is no constraint. Sharding main issue is that\ncross shard complex queries.\n\nmongo DB, dynamo: schemaless and good on writes.\ndynamo DB: partition key and sorting key.\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "27QC9UgFKt-jexyefXFHZ",
      "type": "text",
